Muslim pilgrims from all around the world circle around the Kaaba at the Grand Mosque, in the Saudi city of Mecca on September 14, 2016. RIYADH - Saudi Arabia says the Hajj pilgrimage will be held this year. But it's not yet clear whether foreign nationals will be allowed into Saudi Arabia to be part of this year's event. READ: Mecca reopens for limited 'umrah' pilgrimage The country says it has met the health and safety requirements for the gathering. Hajj attracts millions of people from across the world. For the past two years, the pilgrimage to Mecca was reduced to a few thousand.